üë©‚Äçüéìüë©‚ÄçüéìClass of 2020 üë©‚Äçüéìüë©‚Äçüéì
SENIOR SPOTLIGHT

Meet Erica Cullens. Erica has attended South Haven Schools since she was in 8th grade. Her favorite memory from high school was her junior year during softball season. She shared, "we may not have won every game but we gave it our all. I loved watching us get better in practice and working harder in games, watching us grow as a team and even closer as friends."

Erica will be attending Cowley County Community College where she will train to become a cosmetologist. When asked who she would thank for getting her here she said, "I have a lot more than one person to thank. I would not have made it this far without my family and teachers pushing me and supporting me all the time. I am very grateful for all of you and a big thank you to my class even though we don't always get along, y'all have been there for me through it all and I really appreciate everyone."

Erica, you will be missed next year. Your perseverance has been admirable and we wish you luck at Cowley!

post_text:
Ode of Remembrance
They went with songs to the battle, they were young.
Straight of limb, true of eyes, steady and aglow.
They were staunch to the end against odds uncounted,
They fell with their faces to the foe.
They shall grow not old, as we that are left grow old:
Age shall not weary them, nor the years condemn.
At the going down of the sun and in the morning,
We will remember them.
-Binyon

USD 509 Driver Education will be July 20th through July 31st. The classroom portion of the class will be daily at 9:00 a.m. followed by scheduled driving time. There will be no classroom instruction on the weekends. Cost of the class will be $185. The course fee will be refunded if the class is cancelled due to Covid-19. There is a mandatory enrollment meeting tentatively scheduled for June 15th at 9:00 a.m. at South Haven High School.
Students interested in taking Driver Education must email Mr. Heater at mikeheater@usd509.org to pre enroll and receive detailed class information. Students must be 14 years old by July 1st, 2020.
